   Country music singer Eddie Rabbitt,
whose 2-year-old son died of liver disease, will act as honorary
chairman of the American Council on Transplantation.
   Timmy Rabbitt died in July 1985 after a transplant at the
University of Minnesota and four other operations.
   The council is a non-profit federation of individuals and
organizations concerned with improving the donation and delivery of
organ and tissue transplants.
   Rabbitt, whose appointment was announced Monday, has recorded a
public service announcement for the council and plans to be in
Washington on April 24 for special council activities as part of
National Organ-Tissue Donor Awareness Week.
