<2ND_LINE>PM-House Fire,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Four Dead, Five Injured In House Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An early morning fire roared through a house
where more than eight people were staying, killing four people and
injuring five, including a firefighter, authorities said.
   An undisclosed number of children were missing, they said.
   The fire broke out about 5:30 a.m. in the two-story house in the
Bayswater section of Queens borough, and spread to a second alarm
before being brought under control shortly before 7 a.m.
   ``Apparently it was a well-advanced fire before units arrived,''
said Deputy Fire Chief John Hart.
   Firefighters who went inside the house ``found one body just
inside the door and three bodies up on the second floor,'' he said.
   A search was under way inside the house for the missing
children, he said.
   Four people inside the house were injured, one possibly
seriously, said Capt. Mark Rothstein of the Emergency Medical
Service, and one firefighter suffered minor injuries.
