<HEAD>Rock Musician Sentenced for Joke at Airport</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. JOHN'S, Newfoundland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A rock guitarist who joked to an
airport security guard about explosives in his luggage pleaded
guilty to mischief charges and was sentenced to six months'
probation.
   Donald William Donahue, 28, of the Toronto band Razorbacks, was
arrested after he told the St. John's Airport guard checking his
hand luggage, ``Don't touch that; it might explode.''
   Donahue, who goes by the stage name Danny Cartwright, was
arrested and charged with mischief over the weekend. He pleaded
guilty in provincial court this week.
   The Razorbacks were on an Atlantic Canada tour with blues-rock
guitarist Stevie Ray Vaughan.
