<HEAD>Report Record Year For London Theaters</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Name in 2nd graf Society of West End Theater is cq.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A record-breaking 11 million people went to
theaters in London's West End last year, it was announced Wednesday.
   The total attendance was 85,000 up on the record year of 1985
and gross box-office revenue at 42 theaters was also a record at
$207 million, according to the Society of West End Theater.
   Louis Benjamin, president of the Stoll Moss group which owns 12
theaters, said that with shows such as ``42nd Street'' and
``Phantom of the Opera,'' this year ``promises to be the best ever
in the history of the company.''
   The 42 theaters staged 16,603 performances in 1987.
