<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Sweden-Drugs     04-06 0180</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Sweden-Drugs,0186</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Arrest 12 in Cracking International Drug Ring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police in four countries arrested 12
people and cracked the largest drug ring based in Sweden,
authorities said Wednesday.
   The latest arrests bring to 15 the number of arrests in the case
since last year. Authorities have also seized 240 pounds of heroin.
   Five ring leaders, all Swedes of Turkish origin, were arrested
at the end of March in Sweden, the Netherlands and West Germany,
said Birger Hemmingsson, who heads Sweden's anti-narcotics division.
   West German police arrested another five ring members on March
28 in Darmstadt and found 55 pounds of heroin, he said. Danish
police arrested a Turkish couple at the same time.
   Italian police last year arrested three Italian members of the
ring in Verona, seizing 187 pounds of heroin, Hemmingsson said.
   The ring was believed to have operated for at least two years,
shipping large amounts of heroin from Turkey to Europe. The
distributor in Turkey has not been arrested, Hemmingsson said.
   He said the drugs were bound for other European countries.
</TEXT>
