<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-Cage     04-06 0161</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Cage,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>John Cage Opera Gets Premiere</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John Cage's only opera, ``Europeras 1 & 2,''
will have its American premiere this summer at the PepsiCo
Summerfare program.
   One hundred forty artists plus technicians are required to put
on the opera, which will be staged in Purchase, north of the city.
   Cage derived conducting, costume choices, stage movement and
some of the music by consulting the ancient Chinese fortune-telling
I Ching, much as he does when composing for dance. A computer
program that adds time to spatial dimensions helped as well.
   Summerfarem, which runs July 8-31, will present the Frankfurt
(Germany) Opera's production of the Cage work.
   It also is staging an opera in which Director Peter Sellars
moves the action from the time and place written in the libretto.
This summer he will set ``The Marriage of Figaro'' in the Penthouse
at Manhattan's Trump Tower, apparently because that's a place where
people still have uniformed servants.
</TEXT>
