<TEXT>
   A Roman Catholic priest sought on federal drug
trafficking charges has been arrested by Italian police in Bologna,
a federal prosecutor said Wednesday.
   Special Italian drug officers arrested the Rev. Lorenzo Zorza at
the home of a woman they described as an Italian art restorer, U.S.
