<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Obit-Pickens     04-06 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Obit-Pickens,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Father Of T. Boone Pickens Jr. Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMARILLO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thomas Boone Pickens, father of oilman
and investor T. Boone Pickens Jr., died in his sleep Monday. He was
90.
   Pickens had worked for Phillips Petroleum Co. and was a
shareholder of his son's Mesa Limited Partnership.
   The elder Pickens joined the U.S. Navy during World War I and
served as chief yeoman of the USS Pensacola.
   After receiving his law degree in 1921 from Cumberland
University at Lebanon, Tenn., he joined a law firm in Holdenville,
Okla. There he married Grace Molonson in 1923. She died in 1977.
   Pickens moved to Amarillo in 1943 and worked for Phillips,
buying oil leases nationwide for the company.
   After retiring in 1959, he formed his own lease-buying business.
   Survivors include his son and five grandchildren.
   Graveside services were scheduled for Wednesday in Llano
Cemetery.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
