<FILEID>AP-NR-04-06-88 1113EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u f PM-Northwest-Seniors     04-06 0338</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Northwest-Seniors,0351</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Northwest Airlines Offers Senior Citizens Age-Matching Discounts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAGAN, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northwest Airlines announced a two-month
discount that will give senior citizens a percentage off their fare
that matches their age.
   For example, a 65-year-old will receive a 65 percent discount
and a 100-year-old will fly free, the airline said Tuesday.
   ``The stock phrase, `I'm not getting older, just better,'
deserves an updating,'' said A.B. Magary, executive vice president
of marketing for Northwest. ``The older you are the greater your
discount gets.''
   The discount, which covers people aged 65 and older, is good
from April 12 through June 8 and applies to all full economy fares
on Northwest's domestic flights. The fares may be used every day
except Fridays and Sundays and May 31, and reservations must be
made and tickets purchased at least seven days in advance.
   Travel must include at least two nights' stay before returning
and must be concluded by June 8.
   Magary said the idea is to stimulate discretionary travel until
the peak summer season begins in June.
   With that goal in mind, Eastern Airlines and Continental
Airlines _ both subsidiaries of giant Texas Air Corp. _ announced
Tuesday that they are reducing fares for the next two months on
tickets carrying restrictions used mainly by vacationers. American
Airlines and United Airlines made similar fare cuts.
   Texas Air's ``spring sales'' are for travel between April 18 and
June 15, with no one-way fare greater than $99 for travel anywhere
in the mainland United States.
   The discount fares carry numerous restrictions and are not
refundable. Tickets must be purchased in the next nine days.
   Magary said Tuesday that Northwest will match the Eastern and
Continental fares in most Northwest markets. Northwest was alone in
offering the senior citizen discounts.
   Magary said another goal of the discount program is to introduce
World-Horizons, a frequent-flier program for seniors modeled after
similar plans at other airlines. Seniors who enroll in the
Northwest plan, which begins June 1, can obtain discounted fares on
many Northwest flights.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
