<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Noon,0388</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices turned slightly lower today, as an
early rally effort faded in lackluster trading.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrial stocks, which rose 16.91
points on Tuesday, was unchanged at 1,997.51 at noon on Wall Street.
   But losers ran slightly ahead of gainers in the overall tally of
New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 612 up, 640 down and
531 unchanged. And several broader market indicators were down
slightly.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 64.48 million shares at
noontime, compared with 63.78 million shares at the same point in
Tuesday's session.
   The stock market opened higher today, but gave up those early
gains as the session wore on.
   ``We had a little buying enthusiasm as a remnant from
yesterday's strong close, but then ran into a lot of resistance,''
said Charles Jensen, chief technical analyst for MKI Securities
Corp. ``Now, we've bogged down here in narrow trading range.''
   Analysts say investors' uncertainty about the direction of the
economy and interest rates have put a damper on stock prices. They
say some investors have also been unable to shake worries inspired
by last October's price crash.
   In the credit markets today, the federal funds rate, a key
short-term interest rate, edged over 7 percent. Rising rates make
bonds a more appealing investment than stocks to some investors.
   F.W. Woolworth was among the most actively-traded stocks on the
NYSE, falling 1| to 55. The stock shot up more than $11 a share in
the previous two sessions after a group led by Dart Group Corp.
Chairman Herbert Haft expressed interest in acquiring a stake in
the retailer.
   A number of utility issues were also among the most active
issues. Illinois Power was off [ at 21], Carolina Power & Light was
unchanged at 33 and Bell South was up \ at 37|.
   Among the most widely-held stocks, American Telephone &
Telegraph was up [ at 27, International Business Machines was down
1] at 106[ and General Electric was off ] at 40\.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
off 0.06 at 146.23. At the American Stock Exchange, the market
value index slipped 0.52 to 294.55.
